HEADWORD: mangrove family
<hw>mangrove family</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A natural family
(<fam>Rhizophoraceae</fam>) of trees and shrubs that usually form dense
jungles along tropical seacoasts. It includes the mangrove
<member><spn>Rhizophora Mangle</spn></member>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

